<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-04T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-04T11:00:00-05:00" n="552" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d552">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 341.115P51/50</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-04T16:00:00+00:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1915, 4 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.45 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2029. Your 1473 and my 1998 of April 27 regarding the <persName>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Joseph W. Fordney</hi></persName>.<note n="1" xml:id="d552fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_376">p.
                                    376</ref>.</note> Have requested Legation at Stockholm to
                                investigate matter of consignee of cargo at Malmö. Understand firm
                                of E. Klingener exists at Goteborg but does not appear as existing
                                at Malmo. Should he have branch house at Malmo will immediately
                                present facts to British Government and request release of vessel
                                and cargo.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>